title: Vaccination Subsidy Scheme 2018/19 (Seasonal Influenza Vaccination)
description:
Middle-aged woman:
(subtitle) The Government has expanded the Vaccination Subsidy Scheme
I’d better get the influenza vaccination at once!
Middle-aged man:
(subtitle) We just turned 50. Are we eligible too?
English MVO: Eligible groups for subsidised influenza vaccination
have been extended to include persons aged 50 or above
Super: Eligible groups include: 
Persons aged 50 or above
Pregnant women
Children aged 6 months to under 12 years (or primary school students)
Persons with intellectual disability 
Persons receiving Disability Allowance
English MVO: Pregnant women, children, persons with intellectual disability and
persons receiving Disability Allowance are also eligible
to receive subsidised influenza vaccination
from private doctors enrolled in the Scheme
 The subsidy has been increased to $210 per dose
 For details, visit chp.gov.hk
Super: Prevent Influenza
Get Vaccinated Now
chp.gov.hk
Centre for Health Protection
Department of Health
channelTitle: 政府新聞處 Information Services Department, HKSARG
